MAGIC ITEMS IN THE DOMAIN SHIRE
=================================
As required, all magical items will be found here. However, if any questions remain, contact the coder, the Liege or Steward of the Shire, or any other member of the domain on at the time (in case of emergency).
 
Magical equipment throughout the Shire->
----------------------------------
 
Weapons:
----------------------------------
Item: Leech, Magebane, jagged black scimitar
Coder: Mayhem
Path name: /d/Shire/mountain/wep/magebane.c
Skill/Stat enhancements: None
Type: Sword
    WC: 52/42
    Hands: Any
    Wield: SS_SWORD > 50 and non-mage  
    Extra: Drains and stores some amount of mana from the enemy 
        on a hit, once the stored energy is enough it increases the
        damage caused by the next blow by delivering a magic shock
        of greater damage then the hit, in addition to the normal damage.
        Checks MAGIC_I_RES_DEATH for mana drain, MAGIC_I_RES_MAGIC
        for the extra damage.
Magic: 78, Enchantment
Resistance: None
Specials: Intelligent, possession attempts. See "Extra" above.
Location: Used by Hzzz (/d/Shire/mountain/npc/hzzz.c)
Notes: Difficult to obtain, although not impossible.
 
Item: Elfblade, gleaming short sword
Coder: Morinir
Path name: /d/Shire/common/weapon/elfblade
Skill/Stat enhancements: None
Type: Sword
    WC: 20/35 or 10/10 if wieled by a goblin. 
    Hands: Any
    Wield: None  
 
Magic: 60, Enchantment
Resistance: None
Specials: Detects orcs/goblins/uruks in the room and adjacent rooms when
          you examine the blade.
Location: Part of a Troll treasure.
 
Item: Giant Black Maul
Coder: Rogon
Path name: /d/Shire/moria/wep/maul.c
Skill/Stat enhancements: None
Type: Poelarm
    WC: 35/45
    Hands: W_LEFT, W_RIGHT, or W_BOTH
    Wield: SS_STR of 100 to wield it two handed
           SS_STR of 140 and SS_DEX of 110 to wield it single handed.  
    Extra: If you do 100 points of damage with this weapon it attempts
           to slay any armour that is in its way damaging the armour
           or breaking it completely. If there is no armour stopping
           the force of this blow double damage is produced.  
Magic: 60, Enchantment
       50, armour-slaying
Resistance: None
Specials: Armour-slaying see Extra.
Location: Used by Ashburz, formally Bolg (/d/Shire/moria/npc/urukcap.c)
Notes: Should be quite difficult to obtain, although not impossible.
 
Item:  Balin's Axe (was Dain's Axe, but he's still alive!)
Coder: Rogon
Path name: /d/Shire/moria/wep/dainaxe.c
Skill/Stat enhancements: None
Type: Axe
    WC: 30/52
    Hands: Both or single-haned
    Wield: SS_AXE > 50 as well as a high int, wis and str... these
           stat requirements are of course lowered for dwarves.  
Magic: 22, Enchantment
       40, orc-slaying
       40, troll_slaying
Resistance: None
Specials: Slays orcs and trolls.
Location: Used by  (/d/Shire/moria/npc/bigtroll.c)
Notes: Difficult to obtain, although not impossible.
 
Item: Excellent Halberd
Coder: Milan?
Path name: /d/Shire/misty/wep/halberd_sup.c
Skill/Stat enhancements: None
Type: Polearm
    WC: 42/52
    Hands: For proper usage W_BOTH
    Wield: No requirements.  
Magic: 10, Enchantment
Resistance: None
Specials: A damage special where the halberd acts on it's own which
          is based off the players strength and polearm skill.
Location: Used by Goblin Lord (/d/Shire/misty/npc/gcave_lord.c)
Notes:    Now GL always wields this weapon, its much harder to get
          to the Goblin Lord, and he breaks weapons instead of hand-
          ing out bleeding wounds.
       
 
